{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52cadb05-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2075"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2075"},"text":"§ 2075.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Bankruptcy rules","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Supreme Court shall have the power to prescribe by general rules, the forms of process, writs, pleadings, and motions, and the practice and procedure in cases under title 11.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Such rules shall not abridge, enlarge, or modify any substantive right.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Supreme Court shall transmit to Congress not later than May 1 of the year in which a rule prescribed under this section is to become effective a copy of the proposed rule. The rule shall take effect no earlier than December 1 of the year in which it is transmitted to Congress unless otherwise provided by law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The bankruptcy rules promulgated under this section shall prescribe a form for the statement required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s707/b/2/C"},"text":"section 707(b)(2)(C) of title 11","children":[],"tail":" and may provide general rules on the content of such statement."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52cadb06-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/623/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–623, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/1001"},"text":"78 Stat. 1001","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tII/s247"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title II, § 247","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2672"},"text":"92 Stat. 2672","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/394/tI/s104/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–394, title I, § 104(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4110"},"text":"108 Stat. 4110","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8/tXII/s1232"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8, title XII, § 1232","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-04-20"},"text":"Apr. 20, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/202"},"text":"119 Stat. 202","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52cadb07-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52cadb08-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52cadb09-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":" inserted at end “The bankruptcy rules promulgated under this section shall prescribe a form for the statement required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s707/b/2/C"},"text":"section 707(b)(2)(C) of title 11","children":[],"tail":" and may provide general rules on the content of such statement.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/394"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–394","children":[],"tail":" amended third par. generally. Prior to amendment, third par. read as follows: “Such rules shall not take effect until they have been reported to Congress by the Chief Justice at or after the beginning of a regular session thereof but not later than the first day of May and until the expiration of ninety days after they have been thus reported.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" substituted “in cases under title 11” for “under the Bankruptcy Act” and struck out provisions directing that all laws in conflict with bankruptcy rules be of no further force or effect after such rules have taken effect."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52cadb0a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52cadb0b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2005 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":" effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-04-20"},"text":"Apr. 20, 2005","children":[],"tail":", and not applicable with respect to cases commenced under Title 11, Bankruptcy, before such effective date, except as otherwise provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/8/s1501"},"text":"section 1501 of Pub. L. 109–8","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52cadb0c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/394"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–394","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1994","children":[],"tail":", and not applicable with respect to cases commenced under Title 11, Bankruptcy, before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1994","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/394/s702"},"text":"section 702 of Pub. L. 103–394","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52cadb0d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s402/d"},"text":"section 402(d) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52cadb0e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Rules Promulgated by Supreme Court","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/tIII/s320"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, title III, § 320","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/357"},"text":"98 Stat. 357","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/98/353/tIII/s320"},"text":"“The Supreme Court shall prescribe general rules implementing the practice and procedure to be followed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s707/b"},"text":"section 707(b) of title 11","children":[],"tail":", United States Code. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2075"},"text":"Section 2075 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, shall apply with respect to the general rules prescribed under this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52cadb0f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Applicability of Rules to Cases Under Title 11","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tIV/s405/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title IV, § 405(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2685"},"text":"92 Stat. 2685","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/95/598/tIV/s405/d"},"text":"“The rules prescribed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2075"},"text":"section 2075 of title 28","children":[],"tail":" of the United States Code and in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1979","children":[],"tail":", shall apply to cases under title 11, to the extent not inconsistent with the amendments made by this Act, or with this Act [see Tables for complete classification of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":"], until such rules are repealed or superseded by rules prescribed and effective under such section, as amended by section 248 [247] of this Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52cadb10-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Additional Rulemaking Power","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tIV/s410"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title IV, § 410","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2687"},"text":"92 Stat. 2687","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/95/598/tIV/s410"},"text":"“The Supreme Court may issue such additional rules of procedure, consistent with Acts of Congress, as may be necessary for the orderly transfer of functions and records and the orderly transition to the new bankruptcy court system created by this Act [see Tables for complete classification of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
